The paper discusses Bayesian agents learning from private signals and the actions of others, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The concept of groupthink and the failure of information aggregation also relates to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social networks (cs.SI). The paper also uses statistical learning techniques, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS).
